<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Supreme" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Supreme</orth> (<emph>súpreme</emph> or <emph>supréme;</emph> cf. Grammatical Observations p. 1413) highest: <cit><quote>the life of purity, the s. fair,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 780" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 780</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>s. head,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.155" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 155</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>s. magistrates,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.3.57" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 3, 57</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the s. King of kings,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 1, 13</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the s. seat,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.118" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 7, 118</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>two authorities, neither s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.110" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 110</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>s. Jove,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 5.3.71" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 71</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>my s. crown of grief,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 1.6.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 6, 4</bibl></cit>.<lb />Substantively: <cit><quote>imperious s. of all mortal things,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 996" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 996</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>